.nav-button {
  padding: 12px 24px;
  font-size: 16px;
  background-color: #2c3e50;
  color: #ffffff;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
}

.nav-button:hover {
  background-color: #1a252f;
}

This CSS demonstrates UI principles: adequate padding for touch targets, readable font size, clear visual contrast, and a hover effect that provides user feedback — all contributing to a better UX.

const button = document.getElementById('action-btn');

button.addEventListener('click', function() {
  this.textContent = 'Added to Cart!';
  this.style.backgroundColor = '#27ae60';
  setTimeout(() => {
    this.textContent = 'Add to Cart';
    this.style.backgroundColor = '#2c3e50';
  }, 2000);
});

This code demonstrates the UX principle of responsive feedback — when a user clicks the button, it immediately changes text and colour to confirm the action, then reverts after 2 seconds. Immediate feedback reduces user uncertainty.

/* Desktop: horizontal navigation */
.nav-menu {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  gap: 20px;
  list-style: none;
}

/* Mobile: vertical navigation */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .nav-menu {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
}

This media query applies the vertical layout when the viewport width is 768px or less (typical tablet/mobile breakpoint). The navigation items stack vertically for easier touch interaction on smaller screens, demonstrating the UX principle of adapting the interface to the user's context and device.

-- Create a read-only user for the 'customer_reports' table
CREATE USER report_viewer IDENTIFIED BY 'SecureP@ssw0rd!';

-- Grant only SELECT (read) permission on the specific table
GRANT SELECT ON enterprise_db.customer_reports TO report_viewer;

-- Verify: This user CANNOT run INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE
-- The following would produce an 'access denied' error:
-- INSERT INTO enterprise_db.customer_reports VALUES (...);

This demonstrates the principle of least privilege — the user 'report_viewer' can only read data from the customer_reports table. They cannot modify, delete, or insert data, and they have no access to other tables. This minimises the potential damage if this account is compromised.
